[2]
Date: 5 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong - Department of Health 5 Apr 2003
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>

[A] Situation report on atypical pneumonia 5 Apr 2003
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
As at 3 PM 5 Apr 2003, an additional 39 patients with symptoms of atypical
pneumonia were admitted to public hospitals. They include 10 healthcare
workers and 7 patients from Amoy Gardens. The remaining 22 were new
patients and contacts of patients with atypical pneumonia.
A total of 107 patients have recovered from atypical pneumonia and have
been discharged from public hospitals. Of them, 8 were discharged today.
Most of the patients currently in hospital are showing positive responses
to the new treatment protocol. 107 patients are receiving treatment in
intensive care unit.
3 male patients all with a history of chronic disease died in hospital
today, bring to 20 the total number of deaths relating to atypical
pneumonia. They include 2 patients, aged 73 and 81, who died in Prince of
Wales Hospital. The third case, a 52-year-old man, died in Princess
Margaret Hospital.
The cumulative number of patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with atypical pneumonia since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows:
(The numbers in bracket are those with pneumonia symptoms)
Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students 192 (192)
56 of the patients were discharged
Patients, family members & visitors 608 (608)
51 of the patients were discharged
Total admission 800 (800)
107 were discharged
[B] DH urges hospital visitors to contact hotline 5 Apr 2003
The Department of Health (DH) on 5 Apr 2003 urged members of the public who
had recently visited Ward E1, E3 and E6 of Alice Ho Miu Ling Nethersole
Hospital in Tai Po and Ward 12A of United Christian Hospital in Kwun Tong
during the following specified periods to contact DH's hotline 187 2222:
A. Ward E1 of Alice Ho Miu Ling Nethersole Hospital:
21 Mar 2003 to 3 Apr 2003
B. Ward E3 of Alice Ho Miu Ling Nethersole Hospital:
23 Mar 2003 to 3 Apr 2003
C. Ward E6 of Alice Ho Miu Ling Nethersole Hospital:
27 Mar 2003 to 3 Apr 2003
D. Ward 12A of United Christian Hospital:
24 Mar 2003 to 2 Apr 2003
The plea was made as DH received report that some staff members of these
wards were suspected to suffer from atypical pneumonia. "Therefore, we
have to locate the visitors to the wards so that we can monitor their
health condition," a DH spokesman added.
The hotline 187 2222 is manned daily from 9 AM to 7 PM.
--
